Puzzle 2
-----------------------

Book 1
1) The first number and the second number should sum to 17
2) Book 3 should say 8 instead of 4 everywhere
3) The code contains an odd number of odd numbers, and an even number of even numbers

Book 2
1) All books should say 5 instead of 7 everywhere
2) Reading each digit out should be 6 syllables
3) If the code is <50000, the code is a perfect cube

Book 3
1) The code is a 7 digit number
2) The second number and third number should sum to 14
3) The last digit is a perfect square

